<h2>Privacy Policy for Paynles Tracker Chrome Extension</h2>
<p><em>Last updated: August 24, 2025</em></p>

<h3>1. Introduction</h3>
<p>At <strong>Paynles.com</strong>, we value your privacy. This policy explains how the <strong>Paynles Tracker Chrome Extension</strong> collects and uses data, and ensures compliance with both the Google Chrome Web Store and Amazon Associates Program requirements.</p>

<h3>2. What Data We Collect</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Product URLs, ASINs, or metadata from supported product pages (e.g., Amazon)</li>
    <li>Pricing, titles, descriptions, and product images</li>
    <li>User-selected actions (e.g., "track this item")</li>
</ul>
<p>No personally identifiable information (PII) is collected by the extension itself.</p>

<h3>3. Why We Collect This Data</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To track product pricing trends</li>
    <li>To suggest cheaper alternatives or better-value bundles</li>
    <li>To notify users about price drops or matching deals</li>
    <li>To sync selected items to the user's Paynles.com account (if logged in)</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. How Data is Stored and Handled</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Data is stored locally in the browser using Chrome's <code>storage</code> API</li>
    <li>Optional sync to Paynles.com if signed in (secured and encrypted)</li>
    <li>We do not share or sell your data with any third party</li>
    <li>We do not track or record activity outside supported product pages</li>
</ul>

<h3>5. Chrome Permissions</h3>
<p>This extension uses the following permissions:</p>
<ul>
    <li><code>storage</code>: to save your product tracking preferences</li>
    <li><code>activeTab</code> and <code>scripting</code>: to extract product info from open pages</li>
    <li><code>clipboardWrite</code> (if applicable): to allow copying tracked product info</li>
</ul>

<h3>6. Affiliate Disclosure (Amazon Requirement)</h3>
<p>Some links used by the extension may direct you to Amazon.com or other retailers using affiliate referral codes. As an Amazon Associate, <strong>Paynles.com</strong> may earn a commission from qualifying purchases.</p>
<p>We do not share your data with Amazon. Their own cookies and tracking may apply once you leave our extension.</p>

<h3>7. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
<p>The extension itself does not use cookies or third-party trackers. However, when visiting retailer sites (like Amazon), those sites may apply cookies according to their privacy policies. We do not access, modify, or interfere with these cookies.</p>

<h3>8. Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have questions about this policy or how your data is handled, contact us at:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@paynles.com">support@paynles.com</a></li>
    <li>Web: <a href="https://paynles.com/Home/Contact">https://paynles.com/Home/Contact</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>9. Policy Updates</h3>
<p>This policy may be updated as the extension evolves. Significant changes will be communicated via the extension or the Paynles.com site.</p>
